  Text: |-
    Not suitable as pets
    Can withstand wide swings in water quality and forage effectively in low visibility
    Swims: bottom
    Highly specialized respiratory system
    Generally sedentary, secretive, and cover-oriented; emerges more in low light
    Only in certain parts of Africa, because of their abundance and size, are they of any value to humans as food. The South American lungfish, which is obtained in the same manner, is eaten locally.
